headline: Tractor Supply (TSCO) Announces US$0.23 Quarterly Dividend Payout
summary: Tractor Supply (TSCO) announced its quarterly cash dividend of $0.23 per share, enhancing its commitment to shareholder value. Over the last quarter, the company's share price rose by 17.00%, fueled not only by this dividend affirmation but also by Q2 earnings that showed modest improvements in sales and net income. headline: 2 Reasons to Like TSCO and 1 to Stay Skeptical
summary: Tractor Supply has had an impressive run over the past six months as its shares have beaten the S&P 500 by 6.1%. The stock now trades at $60.20, marking a 10.6% gain. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
